com.facebook.buck.android.resources

Class ResTableTypeSpec

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.android.resources.ResChunk
      • com.facebook.buck.android.resources.ResTableTypeSpec

  • public class ResTableTypeSpec
extends ResChunk
    ResTableTypeSpec is a ResChunk specifying the flags for each resource of a given type. These flags specify which types of configuration contain multiple values for a given resource. A ResTableTypeSpec consists of: ResChunk_header u16 type u16 header_size u32 chunk_size u8 id u8 0x00 u16 0x0000 u32 entry_count

    This is then followed by entry_count u32s giving the flags for each resource of this type.

    In practice, this is then followed by a ResTableType for each configuration that has resources of this type. For convenience, those are considered to be part of the ResTableTypeSpec.

      • getTotalSize

        public int getTotalSize()
        Description copied from class: ResChunk
        For most chunk's totalSize == chunkSize. For some types, the type logically consists of multiple chunks. In these cases, totalSize is the sum of all the chunks. This is the full size written/read from a buffer for get/put.
